# FIXME

the current situation where the site has routes and is generated using CSR, is not viable on GitLab (and allegedly not on GitHub either)
SSR is not a solution because of Pages
the solution is either using gitlab pages redirects : https://docs.gitlab.com/user/project/pages/redirects/#rewrite-all-requests-to-a-root-indexhtml
or to use SSG (which Angular calls prerendering) like Ballot does

The color input is not great
It is very heavy for the use we have of it
It displays information that we don't need and that are a distraction

The layout is kinda terrible
In the narrow version, it is too narrow and doesn't make good use of the available room
The narrow version could wrap but that would probably be detrimental to the understandability of the ordering of the parties
In the large version, it is too compressed because there's not enough room
In both versions, the border color jumping around depending on the border width is not great

The preset loading does not check anything about the loaded data.
This breaks the page when it happens (for instance loading an arch preset in westminster or vice versa).
